Wow, really enjoyed the Leonard Cohen track. One thing missing in this thread though ... the pure word economy. That song is only one of Cohen's immense catalog of moments where you have to pause and think.

Seeing a lot of Number One Ones with a question embedded. To answer that question (yes, that's a vote for Number One), FIRST IS FIRST.

Pity that FAC isn't as timeless as quite a few of these. And lyrical content is varied. Artists range from Greta Van Fleet (presumably, a group) to Leonard Cohen to Judy Mowatt.

Now that I'm going through these chronologically, I love hearing the sources I'm familiar with used as references.
